                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.74/218: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-02-10T11:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 10, 1922—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 12—11:49 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>43. Representative of Ministry of Communications calling at the Legation with
                    telegrams from Chinese delegates Washington Conference <pb facs="0966" n="846"
                        xml:id="pg_846"/> states Danish Great Northern Telegraph Company making
                    representations to the Ministry pointing out failure of the Federal Company to
                    execute contract asserting categorically that Federal Company will be unable to
                    raise the capital and urging that the Great Northern be allowed to take over
                    Federal contract under guarantee of execution. Director General of Telegraphs
                    returning evasive replies.</p>
                <p>Chinese still perturbed at reported international commission for wireless and
                    disappointed and uneasy at failure even to commence Federal contract.</p>
                <p>Director General particularly anxious to learn method and progress of Federal
                    Company bond issue. If the Department could telegraph reassuring information it
                    would relieve an embarrassing situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
